## Final report

### File edited
- `proofs/lean/extraction/Chacha20Obligations.lean`

### Build status
`lake build` succeeds with exit code 0 and exactly the 5 expected `sorry` warnings — one per obligation. No errors, no unexpected warnings.

### Sub-goals attempted and unresolved
I made concrete tactic attempts on every obligation; **all five remain as `sorry` with first-person admissions and structural unblocks documented in their docstrings**. No obligation was deleted, weakened, restated, or supplemented by an axiom.

Per-obligation attempts (each documented as inline comments in the proof body):

| # | Theorem | Attempts | Outcome |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `chacha20_length_eq_input` | `hax_mvcgen`; `unfold; simp only [bind_pure_comp]`; structural break-out by induction on `m.val.size / 64` | All failed — `mvcgen` needs Hoare-triple form, `simp made no progress`, structural route needs ~12 missing helper lemmas |
| 2 | `chacha20_involution` | existential intro via `chacha20_length_eq_input`; `unfold; mvcgen`; case-split on `m.val.size = 0` | All blocked — depends on the length sorry, mvcgen mismatch, empty case still needs `chacha20_init` reduction |
| 3 | `chacha20_encrypt_block_matches_full` | `unfold` + `simp [chacha20_update]`; `cases h_unsize`; hand-unfold one step of `chacha20_update_blocks` | `partial_fixpoint` not unfolded by simp; no `unsize` inversion lemma; no `try_into ∘ unwrap` inverse lemma |
| 4 | `chacha20_encrypt_last_matches_full` | case split on `< 64` vs `= 64`; `unfold; simp [chacha20_update]`; extract size from length theorem | All blocked for the same reasons — case-split adds no power, partial_fixpoint opaque, length sorry blocks dependent extract |
| 5 | `chacha20_rfc8439_kat` | `refine ⟨⟨_, by decide⟩, by native_decide, rfl⟩`; bare `decide`; manual round-by-round unfolding | `Decidable` synthesis fails on `partial_fixpoint` body; ≈ 1900 manual reductions infeasible |

### Why the sorries survived
The four property-test obligations and the KAT all reduce to navigating through two `partial_fixpoint` recursive functions (`chacha20_rounds_at`, `chacha20_update_blocks`) and seven nested `fold_range`-based helpers (`to_le_u32s_3/8/16`, `u32s_to_le_bytes`, `xor_state`, `add_state`, `update_array`). The Hax prelude provides only the *Hoare-triple* `fold_range_spec_*` lemmas (designed for `hax_mvcgen` on `⦃P⦄ … ⦃Q⦄` goals); the obligations are stated as bare `RustM` equalities + existentials, so the triple lemmas don't apply directly.

The closest reference pattern (`clever_025_remove_duplicates_modified`, 1246 lines, one level of recursion) and the largest one (`run_utf8_validation_u8_modified`, 3650 lines, one level over a byte slice) each handle a problem one to two orders of magnitude smaller than chacha20's nested-recursion-plus-bit-vector-arithmetic structure. The structural unblocks I named (e.g. an `unsize_size` inversion lemma, a `chacha20_update_blocks_one_step` reducer, a `Decidable` instance for `partial_fixpoint` equality, an `update_array_correctness` byte-wise spec) would each be feasible in 50–200 lines independently, but the full chain is out of reach within this session's budget.
