### Sub-goals left as `sorry` with technical reason

| # | Theorem | Why `sorry` survived |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `chacha20_length_eq_input` | Requires TOTALITY of the entire `chacha20` call graph (no precondition restricts the input). Each of `chacha20_init`, `chacha20_double_round` (8 × `chacha20_quarter_round` × 4 × `chacha20_line`), the 10-step `chacha20_rounds_at` `partial_fixpoint`, the four `hacspec_helper` `fold_range` loops, and the recursive `chacha20_update_blocks` `partial_fixpoint` would each need its own no-overflow + in-bounds totality proof, plus a length-tracking invariant. Multiple thousands of lines of fold-induction infrastructure. Structural unblock named in the docstring: a separately-proved `chacha20_total + length` theorem in the prelude. |
| 2 | `chacha20_involution` | Depends on #1 plus the cryptographic involution property — `xor_state_involution`, `chacha20_core_keystream` (keystream depends only on `(ctr, st0)`), and a `chacha20_update_blocks_involution` companion. Effectively a full ChaCha20 functional-correctness proof. Structural unblock named in the docstring. |
| 4 | `chacha20_encrypt_last_matches_full` | Three-case split (size 0 / 0<·<64 / =64). For Case A, the `update_array` `fold_range` over an empty range required a `fold_range_empty_eq` equational lemma I could not extract from the `@[spec]`-mediated definition; Cases B and C add further `try_into`/`unwrap` and `extract`-equality reasoning. Structural unblock named in the docstring: a `update_array_eq_def` lemma + `fold_range_empty_eq` helper. |

